TITLE: Implementing Rate Limiting in Javalin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use Javalin's built-in naive rate limiter to restrict the number of requests per time unit. It demonstrates limiting requests and customizing the key function used for rate limiting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/javalin/website/blob/master/pages/docs/docs.md#2025-04-08_snippet_48

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
app.get("/", ctx -> {
    NaiveRateLimit.requestPerTimeUnit(ctx, 5, TimeUnit.MINUTES); // throws if rate limit is exceeded
    ctx.status("Hello, rate-limited World!");
});

// you can overwrite the key-function:
RateLimitUtil.keyFunction = ctx -> // uses (ip+method+endpointPath) by default
```

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
app.get("/") { ctx ->
    NaiveRateLimit.requestPerTimeUnit(ctx, 5, TimeUnit.MINUTES) // throws if rate limit is exceeded
    ctx.status("Hello, rate-limited World!")
}

// you can overwrite the key-function:
RateLimitUtil.keyFunction = { ctx -> } // uses (ip+method+endpointPath) by default
```

