TITLE: Using Cookie Store to Pass Data Between Servers in Javalin
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use Javalin's cookie store to store and retrieve data between different servers. Various data types (strings, integers, and lists) can be stored and later retrieved from a completely different server instance since the cookie is stored on the client side.
SOURCE: https://github.com/javalin/website/blob/master/pages/docs/docs.md#2025-04-08_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
serverOneApp.post("/cookie-storer", ctx -> {
    ctx.cookieStore().set("string", "Hello world!");
    ctx.cookieStore().set("i", 42);
    ctx.cookieStore().set("list", Arrays.asList("One", "Two", "Three"));
});
serverTwoApp.get("/cookie-reader", ctx -> { // runs on a different server than serverOneApp
    String string = ctx.cookieStore().get("string")
    int i = ctx.cookieStore().get("i")
    List<String> list = ctx.cookieStore().get("list")
});
```

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
serverOneApp.post("/cookie-storer") { ctx ->
    ctx.cookieStore().set("string", "Hello world!")
    ctx.cookieStore().set("i", 42)
    ctx.cookieStore().set("list", listOf("One", "Two", "Three"))
}
serverTwoApp.get("/cookie-reader") { ctx -> // runs on a different server than serverOneApp
    val string = ctx.cookieStore().get("string")
    val i = ctx.cookieStore().get("i")
    val list = ctx.cookieStore().get("list")
}
```

