TITLE: Creating a Simple Javalin Plugin without Configuration
DESCRIPTION: A basic implementation of a rate limiting plugin named 'Ratey' that has no configuration and no context extension. It limits all requests after a hardcoded count of 100.
SOURCE: https://github.com/javalin/website/blob/master/pages/plugins/how-to.md#2025-04-08_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class Ratey : Plugin<Void>() {
    var counter = 0

    override fun onInitialize(config: JavalinConfig) {
        config.router.mount { router ->
            router.before { ctx ->
                if (counter++ > 100) {
                    throw TooManyRequestsResponse()
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
class Ratey extends Plugin<Void> {
    int counter;
    @Override
    public void onInitialize(JavalinConfig config) {
        config.router.mount(router -> {
            router.before(ctx -> {
                if (counter++ > 100) {
                    throw new TooManyRequestsResponse();
                }
            });
        });
    }
}
```

