TITLE: Configuring Maven Shade Plugin for Javalin Application
DESCRIPTION: This XML configuration adds the Maven Shade Plugin to the pom.xml file. It creates a shaded JAR containing all dependencies and specifies the main class of the application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/javalin/website/blob/master/_posts/tutorials/2022-10-30-javalin-docker-example.md#2025-04-08_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: xml
CODE:
```
<plugin>
    <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
    <artifactId>maven-shade-plugin</artifactId>
    <version>3.4.1</version>
    <configuration>
        <transformers>
            <transformer
                implementation="org.apache.maven.plugins.shade.resource.ManifestResourceTransformer">
                <mainClass>app.Main</mainClass> <!-- Here you should put the main class of your application -->
            </transformer>
        </transformers>
        <filters>
            <filter> <!-- This filter is needed to avoid a bug in the shade plugin -->
                <artifact>*:*</artifact>
                <excludes>
                    <exclude>META-INF/*.SF</exclude>
                    <exclude>META-INF/*.DSA</exclude>
                    <exclude>META-INF/*.RSA</exclude>
                </excludes>
            </filter>
        </filters>
    </configuration>
    <executions>
        <execution>
            <phase>package</phase>
            <goals>
                <goal>shade</goal>
            </goals>
        </execution>
    </executions>
</plugin>
```

