TITLE: Implementing JWT Token Issuance Endpoint in Javalin
DESCRIPTION: Java code that creates a GET endpoint for issuing JWT tokens to authenticated users, including the user's principal and roles in the token payload.
SOURCE: https://github.com/javalin/website/blob/master/_posts/tutorials/community/2021-04-16-javalin-sureness-example.md#2025-04-08_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
// issue jwt rest api
app.get("/auth/token", ctx -> {
    SubjectSum subjectSum = SurenessContextHolder.getBindSubject();
    if (subjectSum == null) {
        ctx.result("Please auth!");
    } else {
        String principal = (String) subjectSum.getPrincipal();
        List<String> roles = (List<String>) subjectSum.getRoles();
        // issue jwt
        String jwt = JsonWebTokenUtil.issueJwt(UUID.randomUUID().toString(), principal,
                "token-server", 3600L, roles);
        ctx.result(jwt);
    }
});
```

